Macron products have 3 different wearabilities: Body, Slim and Regular.
A bodysuit is a skin-tight garment that covers the body highlighting its contours. The lightweight and elasticity of the fabrics used facilitate movement. A bodysuit usually lends itself very well to sportswear.
The Slim line garments are quite tight fitting, not too tight and not too thick. These garments follow the contours of the body without constraining it which means they are comfortable.
The Regular fit line ensures a comfortable and generous fit thanks to the choice of cuts and fabrics.

6 Evan Rachel Wood Wedding Dress Look-Alikes!

For a quiet California ceremony on October 30, 2012, Evan Rachel Wood married Jamie Bell in a custom Carolina Herrera gown. Jealous? We hear it was a classic lace mermaid gown with a striped sash at the waist – no colored dress here. Ms. Herrera also designed Bella Swan’s Twilight gown for Breaking Dawn – Part 1. We can’t wait to see this one!

1 of 7

Check out these 6 look-alike gowns!

2 of 7

Carolina Herrera

This figure-flattering silhouette is just what we envision for the beautiful Mrs. Bell. It's classic and stunning (especially from behind).
Photo: Courtesy of Pronovias
3 of 7

Elie Saab for Pronovias

Dreamy? We think yes. This lace gown is airy and fit for a princess.
Photo: Courtesy of Ines Di Santo
4 of 7

Ines Di Santo

This lace mermaid has cap sleeves, like Evan's, and a low back that will catch everyone's attention.

10 Brown Lip Shades You Should Try This Fall

brown lips
Photos via Instagram


Brown lip colors are definitely on trend, but could possibly be one of the most challenging looks to pull off. 

The wrong shade of brown could leave your lips looking muddy or bland.  You also run the risk of looking washed out depending on your complexion and the shade you choose.  “The best way to test shades is to try colors on and photograph them to see what looks best,” says Beauty Artist, Yetty Bames.

We found a few beauties on Instagram who did the work to make your decision making a little less of a mission.


Noelle opted for “Deep Love” matte lipstick and Chestnut liner by MAC.

A photo posted by @malimahalia on


Mali is wearing the Endless Stay Liquid Lip Tint by Manhattan in “Soft Nude.”  The color has beautiful hints of plum and wears as a nice deep brown depending on your complexion.


Don’t be afraid to bring the drama when you chose your perfect shade of brown!  Anneka is wearing “Damned” by Kat Von D.

  Dominique smudged on Milani Cosmetics’ Lip Cream in “Crush,” a brown shade that wears as a deep burgundy on her complexion.  “I love this lip cream because it has great pigmentation, it’s light weight, isn’t too fast drying so you have time to work with applying, is a matte finish, and it’s a great color for fall,” she says.


Breonna is rocking @queenieskincosmetics’ lipstick in “Chocolate,” a shade that’s true to it’s name.

A photo posted by Ize Osemwota (@izefeno) on

  Ize shows us how to wear a nude-ish brown by outlining her lips with “Truffle Raine” by Coloured Raine then mixing in Kat Von D’s “Lolita” in the middle.

A photo posted by Cedes (@cedes_doee) on


Mercedes is wearing Wet n Wild lip pencil in “Dark Brown.”  “I love using this brown lip pencil as lipstick because it gives me a true matte brown that puts me in the mood for fall, she says.

A photo posted by Lonyea Maiden (@makeupbylonn) on

  Lonyea Maiden is wearing Colourpop Cosmetics’ “Limbo.”  “It works for me because it stays put all day and night.  It’s the perfect shade of brown for my skin tone, not too dark and not too light!

A photo posted by Seebybeauty (@seebybeauty) on


To get this perfect shade of of brown, use “Bespoken” lip liner by MAC.

A photo posted by Doni (@donidarkowitz) on


Try “Choco-liscious” by Revlon like Tajia did here. “I like it because I’ve been searching for the perfect shade of brown for my skin tone for a long time and this is the closest I’ve gotten. I like to put setting powder over it sometimes to make it matte.”

It is formulated with 4 simple ingredients:  Aloe Vera, Lavender and Lemongrass Essential Oils, and Alcohol.

The skin-soothing Aloe Vera leaves your hands soft and hydrated, regardless of how frequently you spray them.

The scent of the essential oils makes you want to sanitize your hands on a regular basis, and brings moments of quiet to your day.

75% isopropyl alcohol kills 99.99% of germs.

We are also supporting a local business, as the lavender oil comes from a farm here in North Texas, where no pesticides are used in the growing process.
